author: @stfu492
text: The song “Bittersweet” expresses the conflict between the sweetness of newly-discovered love and the sting of friendship among a group of three longtime friends by tracing the delicate trails of emotion to the place where they cross. WONWOO and MINGYU helped write the lyrics, which illustrates the dilemma “between love and friendship.”Featuring in the song with her unrivaled vocal timbre is artist Lee Hi, adding a sense of maturity to WONWOO and MINGYU’s masculine vocals. The result is such perfect musical chemistry that this highlight is not to be missed.

author: @bjt7117
text: Their vocal textures all layer so well together! Mingyu's has this sort of.. smoky rocker vibe(?) that sounds so cool when he sings in moodier tones like this. Wonwoo has a similar sort of rock vibe, (maybe i'm just thinking of "Trauma" rock version lol), but Wonwoo's is a slightly rougher type of sound. And then with Leehi's sweet voice mixed in, like water, it really feels like a rainy day where the rain washes over the grit of a gritty road. Neon lights and late night bars with dark windows. They paint such a picture with their vocals alone. It's so lovely. ㅠㅠ
